channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Gaza death toll surpasses 40,000 in grim milestone, says Hamas-run Health Ministry
item.description: The war in Gaza has hit another grim milestone after the Hamas-run Health Ministry said the death toll had passed 40,000 since the start of the war on Oct. 8.

item.title: A doctor who says he's reversed his age by 20 years eats these 7 foods every week to boost his longevity
Details emerge after doctor raped, killed in India as thousands protest
item.description: The discovery of the 31-year-old doctor's brutalized body at a state-run hospital has sparked nationwide protests.

item.title: Russian court sentences American Ksenia Karelina, former ballerina, to 12 years
item.description: A former ballerina who lives in California, Ksenia Karelina, was arrested in January and charged with treason, according to Russian state media and the court.

item.title: A Ukrainian soldier said Russian troops in Kursk were 'sitting in the forest and drinking coffee,' unaware they were being invaded
Russian-American Ksenia Karelina sentenced to 12 years in Russian prison
item.description: Russian-American Ksenia Karelina was sentenced by a Russian court to 12 years in prison after pleading guilty to treason earlier this month.

item.title: Arizona man pleads guilty over threatening to kill FBI agents, politicians
item.description: An Arizona man pleaded guilty to making threats against federal officials on Tuesday, having urged fellow social media users to shoot FBI agents and attack politicians.

item.title: Ukraine gambled on an incursion deep into Russian territory. The bold move changed the battlefield
Oklahoma city to pay over $7 million to cleared former death row inmate
item.description: Edmund, Oklahoma has agreed to pay more than $7 million to a former death row inmate who was exonerated after nearly 50 years in prison, making him the longest-serving inmate to be declared innocent of a crime.

item.title: Backpacker dies after suffering 'sudden medical complications' at national park
item.description: A 37-year-old backpacker has died after suffer “sudden onset medical complications” while hiking at a national park in Michigan, authorities said.

item.title: Black box shows Brazil plane crashed 1 minute after pilots sensed trouble, local media says
RFK Jr. attempted to arrange meeting with Harris, sources say
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris and her advisers have not responded to Robert F. Kennedy Jr. with an offer to meet or shown interest in the proposal, according to one source.

item.title: Alabama Supreme Court authorizes third nitrogen gas execution
item.description: Alabama has authorized the execution of a third person by nitrogen gas

item.title: US Army invests billions to battle highly invasive species wreaking havoc on state waterways: 'A significant victory'
Gena Rowlands, acting legend and star of "The Notebook," dies at 94
item.description: Gena Rowlands, hailed as one of the greatest actors to ever practice the craft, died at 94 on Wednesday, her representatives confirmed.
